posts.content: Before coming to Stanford, Andrew Grotto was the senior director for cybersecurity policy at the White House. His portfolio spanned a range of cyber policy issues and he’s played a key role in shaping cyber policy in both the Obama and Trump administrations. Tune in as he sits down with the Stanford School of Engineering’s Russ Altman to discuss the cybersecurity of critical infrastructure.  The Future of Everything airs weekends on SiriusXM channel 121. To listen to past episodes, visit http://stanfordradio.stanford.edu

posts.content: "WheelSwap" uses VR headsets so cyclists can see a driver's point of view of sharing the road with bikes and includes experiences like cyclists riding the wrong way down a one-way street, running a red light or swerving in front of a car. Drivers can use the experience to see what it's like for cyclists when cars pass too closely, change lanes without a signal or open doors in a rider's path.
